## Module 4: Backend Services & API Design

We don't write spaghetti code. We use a **three-tier architecture**.

### 1. API Route Handlers
In the App Router, API endpoints live in `src/app/api/.../route.ts`. 
The API Route has ONE job: Extract the request body, validate it with Zod, pass it to a Service, and return a JSON response.

### 2. The Service Layer
All database queries live in `src/services/`. 
For example, if you want to find an appointment, you don't write `SELECT * FROM...` in the API route. You call `AppointmentService.getAppointmentById(id)`. 
*Why?* If we ever change our database (e.g., switch to PostgreSQL), we only have to change the code in `src/services/`. The API routes remain completely untouched.

