## Module 7: Frontend Architecture & UI/UX

A powerful backend needs a beautiful frontend.

### 1. Server vs. Client Components
By default, Next.js components are **Server Components**. They run on the server and send HTML to the browser. We use these for dashboards to fetch data directly from the DB very quickly.
When we need interactivity (button clicks, form typing, states), we put `'use client'` at the top of the file to make it a **Client Component**.

### 2. Form Handling
Building forms is notoriously hard. We use the golden trio:
* **react-hook-form:** Manages the form state (typing, submitting) without re-rendering the whole page.
* **Zod:** We use the exact same Zod schema from our backend to validate the form *before* it even sends a request.
* **shadcn/ui:** Provides the accessible `<Form>`, `<Input>`, and `<Label>` components.

### Summary
You now understand the architecture of Sethro Medical Center! The data flows from the React Client Forms, through the Next.js API Routes (validated by Zod), into the Service Layer, and finally into the highly-relational MySQL database.
